1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on spoken language understanding (SLU) and language transferring for SLU systems. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes the use of reinforcement learning (RL) to finetune the adapted translator. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques for language transferring. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is possible as the paper may involve the use of neural networks for SLU. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with spoken language understanding.
